                    <h2>What is the KnocScore?</h2>
                    <p>
                        The KnocScore functions similarly to a credit score but focuses on evaluating an individual's
                        knowledge and competence within a particular field. Developed to provide a standardized assessment
                        of professional expertise, the KnocScore offers a tangible way to demonstrate proficiency and
                        authority in specific knowledge domains. This score can be particularly influential during job
                        applications, promotions, and professional networking.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="after">Using KnocScore to Secure High-Paying Jobs</h2>
                    <h3>Profile Building and Enhancement</h3>
                    <p>
                        <b>Create a Comprehensive Profile:</b> Creating a great impression with your KnocScore will mean
                        that you will want to ensure that your KnocScore is thorough, reflecting all your verifiable
                        qualifications, certifications, and achievements are listed. Stay up to date by signing up as
                        this may impact your ability to add new points in your domains of expertise.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Active Engagement:</b> Participate in forums and discussions within your field. This is a great
                        way to gain peer recognition and post about your qualifications. If you write articles or blogs,
                        you may include your KnoCscore as unquestionable validation of your knowledge.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Resume and Online Profiles</h3>
                    <p>
                        <b>Integrate your score:</b> Clearly display your KnocScore on LinkedIn, professional websites,
                        and your resume. This score, when highlighted, immediately informs potential employers of your
                        verified expertise.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Keep your KnoC up to date</h3>
                    <p>
                        If there is information that is not included in your KnocScore, ensure that it is included by updating
                        it frequently. You may need to check with LinkedIn Jobs to ensure your latest data is included.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-5" col-sm-6>
                    <h3>Strategic Networking</h3>
                    <p>
                        <b>Leverage validation in Introductions:</b> Attend industry conferences and workshops to connect
                        with peers and influencers who can further endorse your skills. Many jobs come from recommendations
                        and name recognition. KnocScore will help your name stick in the memory of a future hiring manager if
                        there is a key domain or skill that the individual is searching for.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Networking Events:</b> Use your KnocScore as a benchmark when making cold
                        introductions in professional settings. A high score can serve as a conversation starter and a
                        testament to your expertise.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Personal Branding</h3>
                    <p>
                        <b>Social Media Utilization:</b> Use platforms like LinkedIn and Twitter not just for posting
                        content but also for interacting with key industry figures. This increases your visibility and
                        your KnocScore can add credibility to your voice.
                    </p>
                    <h3>Job Application Process</h3>
                    <p>
                        <b>Highlight KnocScore on Resumes and LinkedIn:</b> Make your KnocScore a focal point in your
                        applications, particularly when applying for roles that demand high expertise. Add a link to
                        your KnocScore when applying to LinkedIn Jobs.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <b>Interview Preparation:</b> Use your KnocScore to quantitatively back your answers in interviews,
                        adding credibility to your claimed skills and experiences.
                    </p>
                </div>
